==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc}} {{term|ἐσωτερικός||belonging to an inner circle|sc=Polytonic|tr=esōterikos|lang=grc}}, from {{term|sc=polytonic|ἐσωτέρω|tr=esōterō||further inside|lang=grc}}, comparative of {{term|ἔσω||within|sc=Polytonic|tr=esō|lang=grc}}, from {{term|ἐς||sc=Polytonic|tr=es|lang=grc}}, {{term|εἰς||into|sc=Polytonic|tr=eis|lang=grc}} (''esoteric'' originally referred to the secret (vs. public) teachings of Greek philosophers). Compare [[exoteric]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˌes.əʊˈtɛɹ.ɪk/}}, {{SAMPA|/%Es.@U"tEr.Ik/}}
